So we were curious about how the added passages will be during which the main character gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already the case in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole is pulling down due to some unnecessary flaws that have already existed for several years.
These are not really errors but rather the expression of an incomprehensible fanaticism on the part of developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are taken into the adventure whose main character Jack has character problems and to solve them starts participating in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The itinerary is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the planned stages in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are pretty nice even though the graphical technical level is the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in high snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
The tests are further enhanced from time to time by an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to make sure that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Alongside this, the different races are well organized behind each other.
There's only a small number of them, but that's enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the watch (the classic duel with the chronometer) and then again await another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police that enters the game and is trying to make you the situation difficult.
The new ones are the out-of-vehicle passages.
Rather, it’s an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs out in front of someone and you have to help him by pressing the right button at the right time.
There's nothing complicated.
What’s surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be specific there are only three).
As a result, it is as well as this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that please the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is nothing extraordinary at the moment, but it cannot be said to be negative.
When it comes to realistic simulation, you’ll have to go somewhere else.
But although you can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet at the point.
We do not expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight overlaps you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car part in crazy bumps.
Or maybe he's in the middle of a slippery slope.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken the figure or you have come out in the decor the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
Once you have used the 5 restarts you must restart the game from the beginning.
So it’s more a tool, in case something doesn’t go right, that something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and you need to find a solution by remembering the piece of the route in question.
The big hic of this game is that the same actions are in the same places.
For example, there are certain twists that you have to pass in a certain way otherwise this does not pass.
Otherwise you will meet in a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What gets angry is the situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and turn them around or brake them.
It doesn’t matter if you go ahead of him because it’s “calculated” in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Adversaries have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the weather, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This is most annoying at the end of the game when you’re riding on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass before you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of the other vehicles in the opposite direction and you come into collision many times.
You can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have the time to follow everything that's going on.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there’s no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is to change cars during races.
You need to pay attention to the gasoline pumps on the routes as you can change car there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinder cars for highways and super exotic sports cars on high-tech roads, for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places that you know about the adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, various objects begin to unlock:
This connects online with the Autolog feature, which among other things compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other features in the community.
One of the hardest hits to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the metro tunnel (it looks like it) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like it).
Your speed indicator indicates you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway branch that sends you the car directly to the railroad.
At the time of writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about when creating this game or whether the authors really take us for idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra,but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is bothering is that in more extreme situations, the imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true for accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is at your choice.
In order to please as many as possible and especially the younger audience a new soundtrack has been created in the style of "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: Le Run is really confusing.
If the game didn’t have these stupid errors, we could say without fear that it’s the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for the flaws to fall into your eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Students of Velvets in concert with the Choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The festival is composed of two concerts organised on November 17.
"Charles University plays an important role in this festival."
" Among the choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organising team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes concert that takes place with free admission on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the premises located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velours" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of higher schools as well as the choir of Charles University take place.
The objective of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate International Students’ Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Czech High School Union in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the auspices of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and in Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, mixed meetings, a student event and other activities.
Interested people will find all the information on the festival’s website www.festaacademica.cz.
