Famous Scott Peterson scrambled using the past while claiming that his murdered wife was alive, triggering a national search to find her.
Deceptive individuals can also use a remote language: “I haven’t had sexual intercourse with this woman...Mrs. Lewinsky” or completely repeat a difficult question.
The most common verbal indicators are subtle.
Someone can use a lot of "wooden language" when answering a difficult question: "Well...to be honest...if I remember well...to my knowledge."
This makes the response perceptive rather than factual and is often a red flag.
There is no magic formula for the detection of lies, but the development of skills to recognize deception is possible.
