A quick success.
Founded in 2002 in Maiduguri around a mosque, a school and the fundamentalist faith Mohammed Yusuf, Boko Haram - which in Haoussa means "Western education is a sin" - advocates the establishment of an Islamic emirate in northern Nigeria.
In this poor region, the association has achieved rapid success.
